1
00:00:02,599 --> 00:00:04,019
The storm gathers.

2
00:00:04,620 --> 00:00:06,900
Its shadow envelops mankind.

3
00:00:06,919 --> 00:00:08,320
It is the eve of cataclysm.

4
00:00:08,801 --> 00:00:11,621
History is being written.

5
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:16,922
In this film the historic hours of Britain's entry into war are recaptured for you by camera.

6
00:00:16,943 --> 00:00:19,603
How did the people of England act in their great emergency?

7
00:00:20,064 --> 00:00:23,984
Those two memorable days carry a momentous story for future generations.

8
00:00:30,341 --> 00:00:32,203
Krasis har blivit blöjt för en kvartal natt.

9
00:00:32,442 --> 00:00:37,725
I de gamla parlamenten, i hjärtat av demokrati, har medlemmarna varit i säsong under deras normala fredag.

10
00:00:39,267 --> 00:00:45,530
I Downing Street, där primärministern bor, är först den polska ambassadören, sen den germanska Chargé d'Affaires, som är besökare.

11
00:00:45,570 --> 00:00:48,712
Oppositionledare, samt kabinets medlemmar, är kallade in till konferens.

12
00:00:48,792 --> 00:00:51,933
Även om situationen är akut, är krig inte absolut omedelbart, säger vi.

13
00:00:51,973 --> 00:00:54,094
Men hur det ska bli förhållande, kan ingen förstå.

14
00:01:00,164 --> 00:01:02,405
and the preparations for civil defense go on resignedly.

15
00:01:02,426 --> 00:01:04,007
Such scenes as these are familiar to every country in Europe.

16
00:01:04,087 --> 00:01:10,469
It's a tragic thought that the menace of the air should instill the fear of death and destruction into the peoples of all nationalities, whether destined to be friend or neutral.

17
00:01:10,489 --> 00:01:11,331
However, Britain is prepared.

18
00:01:11,350 --> 00:01:14,331
Enormous strides have been made in the years since the September crisis of 1938.

19
00:01:14,352 --> 00:01:16,412
The personnel of the defense forces have increased rapidly in the face of danger.

20
00:01:30,558 --> 00:01:34,980
The balloon barrage and the anti-aircraft units inspire that confidence which comes from knowledge of one's own strength.

21
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,542
Outside Buckingham Palace, the king's sentries pass from peacetime scarlet to service khaki.

22
00:01:37,561 --> 00:01:39,503
The relieving guard wears steel helmets which henceforth will replace the magnificent bearskins.

23
00:02:01,966 --> 00:02:05,149
Världen är inte oavsett, men chanserna för frihet är slända.

24
00:02:05,188 --> 00:02:09,170
Och sjukhuset är evakuerat av deras patienter, unga och äldre, som går till platser av större säkerhet.

25
00:02:09,192 --> 00:02:14,275
Hur patetiskt är det att de unga människorna, i mitten av deras författning, ska ha att förhålla sig till skrämmen som kommer.

26
00:02:14,314 --> 00:02:15,895
Evakueringen ser ut som en stor ordeel.

27
00:02:22,472 --> 00:02:24,734
Det är så skiljt att det finns en plan.

28
00:02:24,813 --> 00:02:28,936
Och så villig var det att få fram att det är minst en tidning av brittiska städer.

29
00:02:28,977 --> 00:02:30,317
Det är därför att det är av rutin.

30
00:02:30,336 --> 00:02:33,780
Departementet av skolbarn var i särskilt en triumf av ordentlig precision.

31
00:02:33,819 --> 00:02:37,581
Från de kraftiga städerna blev barnen i deras tusen hem och föräldrarna bakom.

32
00:02:37,663 --> 00:02:40,324
Och gick bort för att leva i säkerhetszonen under kärlek av deras föräldrar.

33
00:02:53,978 --> 00:02:55,778
And here another concerning thought.

34
00:02:55,879 --> 00:02:57,961
Most of the youngsters went away cheerfully enough.

35
00:02:58,001 --> 00:03:04,104
For them fortunately the whole procedure seemed to hold no terrors and was even regarded as a holiday.

36
00:03:04,125 --> 00:03:10,829
With food and clothing provided by their parents and each carrying a gas mask they entrained for their excitingly unknown destination.

37
00:03:17,164 --> 00:03:18,465
Hur länge ska de vara borta?

38
00:03:18,485 --> 00:03:20,225
Hur länge innan de återkommer att bo under samma djur som deras föräldrar?

39
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:49,364
För most of them it is the beginning of a long period in new surroundings.

40
00:03:49,403 --> 00:04:00,012
The routine of their young lives has been shattered by the high politics of nations by events such as those of which they read in their history books but hardly yet connect with themselves.

41
00:04:00,051 --> 00:04:08,798
It is indeed a strange experience for these thousands of children as well as a great responsibility for those who are charged with their care during these heavy days.

42
00:04:08,818 --> 00:04:15,824
But the appeal of these homeless youngsters was one which captured the sentiments of the country districts and the country districts cared for them with motherly solicitude

43
00:04:19,547 --> 00:04:21,208
The issue is set forth clearly.

44
00:04:45,716 --> 00:04:48,019
Britten rör färg i en kvar för att höra idén.

45
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,783
Traditionen är sätta färdigt, men det kring österdörring stryk för konferens med Mr Chamberlain, en gränsfull fart.

46
00:04:50,803 --> 00:04:51,764
Det är vi enkslös som har blivit främjare igen.

47
00:05:08,473 --> 00:05:12,735
11 o'clock, an hour sacred to Britain for its association with armistice.

48
00:05:12,754 --> 00:05:14,154
11 o'clock on Sunday, September the 3rd.

49
00:05:14,175 --> 00:05:19,476
The government's final warning to Hitler has been ignored and a state of war once more exists between Great Britain and Germany.

50
00:05:19,516 --> 00:05:24,218
Arriving at Westminster to hear the ominous decision, statesmen set a good example thereafter universally followed by carrying their gas masks.

51
00:05:39,019 --> 00:05:40,040
Efter krisen har kabinet reformerats.

52
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:42,401
Mr. Anthony Eden är nu sekreterare för Dominion med speciell tillgång till kabinet.

53
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:44,041
Mr. Churchill, som i 1914, är 1st regeringsledare.

54
00:05:44,062 --> 00:05:45,702
Här är några bilder av tidigare regeringar.

55
00:05:45,742 --> 00:05:47,423
Mr. John Anderson som blir hemsekreterare.

56
00:05:47,504 --> 00:05:50,105
Och Mr. Kingsley Wood som fortfarande är statssekreterare.

57
00:06:09,983 --> 00:06:13,228
Only 25 minutes after war has been declared comes the first air raid warning.

58
00:06:43,420 --> 00:06:47,223
Det här var en möjlighet för brittiska människor att demonstrera deras traditionella kalm mot fara.

59
00:06:47,242 --> 00:06:49,845
Det fanns inga signer av panik.

60
00:06:49,865 --> 00:06:55,327
Män och kvinnor i staden gick snabbt till närmaste fängelset och följde upp i ordentliga processer vid intresset.

61
00:07:05,983 --> 00:07:06,384
Det är allt klart.

62
00:07:06,403 --> 00:07:10,387
Även om alarmet tyckte sig vara en falsk, så var det en snabb minne om vad krig nu betyder för civilerna och en dramatisk introduktion till den nya ordningen av saker.

63
00:07:28,771 --> 00:07:31,853
Evidens that the nation is in earnest can be seen in every street of London.

64
00:07:31,894 --> 00:07:34,495
Notices calling out the territorial army appear on walls and hoardings.

65
00:07:34,516 --> 00:07:39,980
Recruiting depots open for the thousands of men anxious to join the color.

66
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,382
London's taxis are pressed into the service of the fire brigade.

67
00:07:56,494 --> 00:07:59,274
Varför är vi färre än det åker i Gassman?

68
00:08:03,536 --> 00:08:08,598
Mattressen är inståld i en gammalt avsikt för civilstöd som övervånade med vårdverk med rätt.

69
00:08:10,879 --> 00:08:13,079
Men vad görs med lastbiten av här kort?

70
00:08:13,119 --> 00:08:17,321
Det gör en chargé därför att hittills jämför sig en bränsle varje år förbundet.

71
00:08:25,110 --> 00:08:30,576
As for other foreigners in Britain, they have to report of course and satisfy the authorities of their good faith.

72
00:08:30,596 --> 00:08:40,389
War always involves inconveniences for neutrals who are not concerned, but Britain endeavors to extend just and courteous consideration to all the aliens within her gates, including as they do many refugees from countries which have been overrun.

73
00:08:40,408 --> 00:08:42,431
But despite the changes and interruptions of normal life,

74
00:08:46,458 --> 00:08:51,501
The business of the country must go on, and the rush hours show very little diminution of travel.

75
00:08:51,682 --> 00:08:57,664
For many of these people, it's a case of going to the office now and performing air raid precaution duty later in the day.

76
00:08:57,705 --> 00:09:06,688
The common tasks of everyday work are not the least important aspect of the war, which from now on will absorb the whole thoughts of the nation as it musters its manhood in arms.

77
00:09:07,710 --> 00:09:15,274
So within a few days, the people of Britain adapted themselves to the new conditions and set about winning the war with that cheerfulness which never fails them in emergencies.

78
00:09:16,589 --> 00:09:19,658
Vi har sett att eventet skiftar från London till landstinget där Tommy Atkins är på mark.
